# FAAC TODO List

## Tier 1: High Velocity (Minimal change, maximum quality lift)
- [x] **Fix Scalefactor Clamping (-60..60)**: Currently causes massive step-size errors; sounds like harsh ringing/clipping.
- [x] **Adaptive Quantization Rounding**: Implement tonality-aware rounding bias (reducing from 0.4054 to ~0.30 for high-frequency bands) to eliminate metallic ringing.
- [x] **Refined ATH Scaling**: Adjust Absolute Threshold of Hearing for VoIP (16kbps) vs Music bitrates to improve speech clarity.

## Tier 2: Standard Alignment (Improving compliance for stability)
- [ ] **Standard-compliant Scalefactor Encoding**: Fully align with ISO/IEC 14496-3 Section 4.6.2.
- [ ] **Frequency-selective Transient Detection**: Restore/Refine transient detection in `blockswitch.c` to eliminate pre-echo artifacts.
- [ ] **Optimize CPE windows grouping**: Improve stereo image stability.

## Tier 3: Strategic Shifts (Architectural improvements)
- [ ] **Bit Reservoir Control**: Implement proper bit reservoir to handle complex segments without frame drops.
- [ ] **TNS (Temporal Noise Shaping) Expansion**: Test and expand TNS support (arcen, Apr 8th, 2012).
- [ ] **HE-AAC Support**: Strategic addition of High-Efficiency AAC (hans-juergen, Oct 17, 2004).

